- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely because the paper specifically studies the complexity of execution in higher-order programming languages. 
- cs.TL (Theoretical Computer Science) is a broad category that could potentially fit this paper, as it deals with complexity and formal models of computation. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is a possibility because the paper introduces a reduction on finite trees of natural numbers, which could be seen as a formal language or automata. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible, as the paper gives upper bounds on the complexity of certain operations (reductions) on data structures (trees).
